''Ultimate Ninja Storm 4''{{'s}} gameplay is similar to that of previous games in the series, in which players battle each other in 3D arenas. A returning feature, omitted since the original ''Ultimate Ninja Storm'', is the ability to wall-run; players can battle on the sides (walls) of each arena. A major change to the feature is the ability to have one character on the wall and the other on the field; the second player was originally also moved to the wall to keep the battle flowing and the system in check.<ref name="matsuyama">{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/talk-cyberconnect2s-ceo-naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4/|title=We Talk To CyberConnect2's CEO About ''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4''|date=April 13, 2015|access-date=June 28, 2020|website=Siliconera|archive-date=2021-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210630142209/https://www.siliconera.com/talk-cyberconnect2s-ceo-naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4/|dead-url=no}}</ref> The game has the largest number of fighters in series history. Its roster includes 106 fighters from the ''Naruto'' universe (including duplicates of the same characters, such as Naruto (Part 1) and Naruto (Six Paths Sage Mode, or all 7 forms of Obito Uchiha),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/361795/NARUTO_SHIPPUDEN_ULTIMATE_NINJA_STORM_4__ROAD_TO_BORUTO_NOW_AVAILABLE_FOR_NINTENDO_SWITCH_FROM_BANDAI_NAMCO_ENTERTAINMENT_AMERICA_INC.php|title=''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' – Road to Boruto Now Available For Nintendo Switch From Bandai Namco Entertainment America Inc.|website=Gamasutra|access-date=June 29, 2020|date=April 24, 2020|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629134624/https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/361795/NARUTO_SHIPPUDEN_ULTIMATE_NINJA_STORM_4__ROAD_TO_BORUTO_NOW_AVAILABLE_FOR_NINTENDO_SWITCH_FROM_BANDAI_NAMCO_ENTERTAINMENT_AMERICA_INC.php|dead-url=no}}</ref> including characters from the films ''[[The_Last:_Naruto_the_Movie|The Last: Naruto the Movie]]'' (2014) and ''[[Boruto:_Naruto_the_Movie|Boruto: Naruto the Movie]]'' (2015).<ref name="matsuyamainter"/>

The option to select one of three fighting types was removed; it was introduced in  ''[[Naruto_Shippuden:_Ultimate_Ninja_Storm_Revolution|Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm Revolution]]'', restoring the rest of the series' strongest attacks, Ultimate Jutsu and Awakenings system which enhances the fighting capabilities of fighter for a limited time. Another new feature is the ability to swap characters during battle, similar to games such as ''[[Marvel_vs._Capcom_3:_Fate_of_Two_Worlds|Marvel vs. Capcom 3]]''. Awakenings and ultimate jutsus can be shared by switchable characters; players can build their meter with one character and switch to the other, using the same abilities with the other character (which shares the life bar). Also new to the series is the ability to break weapons and armor in free and boss battles with the ability to inflict elemental damage; fire can burn away clothing, but players can get rid of fire by moving quickly across the area or being attacked with water.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hobbyconsolas.com/reportajes/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-avance-entrevista-5111|title=''Naruto Shippuden Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'': Avance y entrevista|date=December 23, 2014|language=es|trans-title=''Naruto Shippuden Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'': Preview and interview|access-date=June 29, 2020|website=Hobby Consolas|author=Quesada, Daniel|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629203622/https://www.hobbyconsolas.com/reportajes/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-avance-entrevista-5111|dead-url=no}}</ref>

A player can initially play the main story mode about the Fourth Shinobi World War set after the events of ''[[Naruto_Shippuden:_Ultimate_Ninja_Storm_3|Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 3]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pushsquare.com/news/2015/07/naruto_shippuden_ultimate_ninja_storm_4s_story_mode_wont_cover_everything|title=Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4's Story Mode Won't Cover Everything|website=Push Square|date=July 14, 2015|author=Ramsey, Robert|access-date=November 2, 2020|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629193049/https://www.pushsquare.com/news/2015/07/naruto_shippuden_ultimate_ninja_storm_4s_story_mode_wont_cover_everything|dead-url=no}}</ref> which it is divided into lineal chapters involving the parallel encounters Naruto and Sasuke have until reuniting. Optional chapters focused on the supporting cast's past are also available to play. Similar to previous ''Storm'' games, the history mode has [[boss_(gaming)|boss]] fights with [[quick_time_events|quick time events]] and [[hack_and_slash|hack and slash]] elements.<ref name="animation"/> When they complete the mode, the player can travel across an [[open_world|open world]] to recreate fights from previous series installments.<ref name="expansiontwo"/> The DLC ''Road to Boruto'' also focuses on the same open world but restricted to Hidden Leaf Village with sidequests being available besides completing its main narrative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pushsquare.com/reviews/ps4/naruto_storm_4_road_to_boruto|title=Naruto Storm 4: Road to Boruto Review (PS4)|website=Push Square|date=February 3, 2017|author=Ramsey, Robert|access-date=November 2, 2020|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629190216/https://www.pushsquare.com/reviews/ps4/naruto_storm_4_road_to_boruto|dead-url=no}}</ref>
