== 遊戲系統 ==
; 隊伍
: 在本作中，可以將複數人員組成一個隊伍<ref name="system1">[http://naruto-game.bngames.net/system/ リーダーチェンジ | バトルシステム] {{Wayback|url=http://naruto-game.bngames.net/system/ |date=20200127004618 }} ナルティメットストーム4公式サイト</ref>。

; 隊長交換
: 在戰鬥中，可以通過在隊長角色與輔助角色之間切換來更改角色<ref name="system1" />。也可以通過隊長更來更換組合<ref name="system1" />。

; 裝備破壞
: 本作ではキャラクターが一定以上の攻撃を受けると装備が破壊される（具体的にはキャラクターの着用しているものがなくなるなど）場合がある<ref name="system2">[http://naruto-game.bngames.net/system/system02.html 装備破壊 | バトルシステム] {{Wayback|url=http://naruto-game.bngames.net/system/system02.html |date=20190906100809 }} ナルティメットストーム4公式サイト</ref>。キャラクターに装備破壊が起きると防御力が落ちるが攻撃力が上がる<ref name="system2" />。

; 屬性效果
: キャラクターの使用する忍術が地形の影響を受ける場合があり、例えばはたけカカシが水面の上で雷切を使用すると雷切の威力が上がる<ref name="system3">[http://naruto-game.bngames.net/system/system03.html 属性効果 | バトルシステム] {{Wayback|url=http://naruto-game.bngames.net/system/system03.html |date=20171122121803 }} ナルティメットストーム4公式サイト</ref>。

; 合體奧義
: チームを特定の組み合わせにして奥義を発動すると合体奥義が発動する<ref name="system4">[http://naruto-game.bngames.net/system/system04.html 合体奥義／連係覚醒 | バトルシステム] {{Wayback|url=http://naruto-game.bngames.net/system/system04.html |date=20171119143618 }} ナルティメットストーム4公式サイト</ref>。組み合わせは複数存在する<ref name="system4" />。

; 連繫覺醒
: 本作にはストームゲージが存在しており、ストームゲージを溜めることでチーム全員が同時に覚醒する事ができる<ref name="system4" />。

== 開發 ==
{{TransH}}
[[File:Hiroshi_Matsuyama_20080704_Japan_Expo_01.jpg|缩略图]]
''Storm 4'' was originally intended to be a [[PlayStation_3|PlayStation 3]] game, but its development was changed to the next generation of consoles to take advantage of hardware capability. [[CyberConnect2|CyberConnect2]] CEO [[Hiroshi_Matsuyama|Hiroshi Matsuyama]] conceived the base narrative, beginning with the fight between Hashirama Senju and Madara Uchiha, over an eight-month period. Each character took fourteen months to be developed. According to Matsuyama, the game's budget was higher than previous titles ({{¥|1.4 billion|link=yes}}) due to the work needed on each character.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://note.com/piroshi3/n/ncb9ec1d9a38c|website=Note|access-date=October 12, 2020|title=第278号『ゲームソフトの工数見積り②ナルト編』|language=ja|trans-title=No. 278 "Estimating Man-hours for Game Software (2) Naruto Edition"}}</ref> Although the previous titles were released for the [[PlayStation_3|PlayStation 3]] and [[Xbox_360|Xbox 360]], ''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' was developed for next-generation consoles as a result of demands by video-game marketers.<ref name="matsuguilt">{{cite web|url=https://www.guiltybit.com/entrevistamos-a-hiroshi-matsuyama-sobre-naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4/|website=Guilty Bit|access-date=June 29, 2020|title=Entrevistamos a Hiroshi Matsuyama Sobre ''Naruto Shippuden Ultimate Ninja Storm 4''|language=es|trans-title=We interview Hiroshi Matsuyama about ''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4''|author=Mora, Manu|date=14 May 2015|archive-date=2020-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200630132844/https://www.guiltybit.com/entrevistamos-a-hiroshi-matsuyama-sobre-naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4/|dead-url=no}}</ref> CyberConnect2 took advantage of the PlayStation 4 and Xbox One hardware to enhance the title's graphics. The team developed the game's narrative to pick up where ''Storm 3'', ''Storm Generations'', and ''Storm Revolution'' left off, and included an adventure mode set after the story.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2015/12/29/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-ps4-interview-talking-story-and-the-series-jump-to-ps4/|website=PlayStationLifeStyle|date=December 29, 2015|access-date=June 28, 2020|title=''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' Interview – Talking Story and the Series' Jump to PS4|author=Briefs, Michael|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629195504/https://www.playstationlifestyle.net/2015/12/29/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-ps4-interview-talking-story-and-the-series-jump-to-ps4/|dead-url=no}}</ref> Matsuyama gathered a number of developers for ''Storm 4'', hoping that the upgraded hardware would complement the [[Naruto|manga]], and said that the its final volume inspired him to design the game.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.famitsu.com/news/201503/31075488.html?page=3|website=Famitsu|access-date=June 29, 2020|title=サイバーコネクトツー松山洋氏が語る『NARUTO-ナルト- 疾風伝 ナルティメットストーム4』の"超アニメ表現"とは？(3/3)|language=ja|trans-title=What is the "super anime expression" of "''Naruto Shippuden Ultimate Storm 4''" that CyberConnect2 Hiroshi Matsuyama talks about? (3/3)|archive-date=2021-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210701143551/https://www.famitsu.com/news/201503/31075488.html?page=3|dead-url=no}}</ref>

Instead of keeping up with secondary characters, CyberConnect2 conceived the Leader System so players could use two independent fighters simultaneously. Matsuyama promised to return to the numbered titles' boss battles because they are popular with fans. Since the manga had finished by the time the game began development, he wanted ''Storm 4'' to have boss fights with visuals surpassing previous installments. Matsuyama cited one boss fight where Naruto Uzumaki, Sasuke Uchiha and Sakura Haruno summon giant animals to combat the Ten-Tails, with Naruto's giant toad Gamakichi "surfing" through the Ten-Tails with a wooden sword. To improve game length, Matsuyama also wanted an online mode. Unique techniques, not present in the manga, were created to fit the pairings which were popular with fans.<ref name="matsuyamainter">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=twQyd8sTpWY|title=''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' - New Features and Changes|work=Bandai Namco Entertainment America|date=April 29, 2015|access-date=June 29, 2020|archive-date=2020-12-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201228050042/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=twQyd8sTpWY|dead-url=no}}</ref>

Matsuyama wanted to add material from the New Generation Project, which was begun by the series when the manga ended its serialization in 2014. The team listened to suggestions by fans, based on the previous games, to make the battle system easier to work.<ref name="express">{{cite web|url=https://ricedigital.co.uk/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-interview/|website=Rice Digital|access-date=June 28, 2020|title=''Naruto Shippuden Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' Interview|archive-date=2021-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628061757/https://ricedigital.co.uk/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-interview/|dead-url=no}}</ref> A mechanic brought from previous games are the walls, where the player can lose a fight by falling from the ring; early in ''Ultimate Ninja Storm 4''{{'s}} development, the staff debated implementing them in boss fights.<ref name="matsuguilt"/> When he saw the finished product, Matsuyama was moved by the final fight between Naruto and Sasuke.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.playstation.com/2016/01/28/the-sound-four-join-naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-on-ps4/|website=PlayStation Blog|access-date=June 30, 2020|date=January 28, 2016|title=The Sound Four Join ''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' on PS4|archive-date=2020-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200630234917/https://blog.playstation.com/2016/01/28/the-sound-four-join-naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-on-ps4/|dead-url=no}}</ref> He sketched the two fighters, intending to put it on the game and promising gamers that they would enjoy the fight.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Hiroshi Matsuyama |user=@PIROSHI_CC2|number=694398006494232576 |date=February 2, 2016 |title=いよいよ発売まで、あと２日！PS4『NARUTOーナルトー 疾風伝 ナルティメットストーム４』！開発しながらも涙を抑えることができませんでした。感動のラストバトルは必見です！極上の物語体験をお見逃しなく！|access-date=July 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |author=Hiroshi Matsuyama |user=@PIROSHI_CC2|number=695064561230032896 |date=February 3, 2016 |title=本日発売！『NARUTOーナルトー ナルティメットストーム４』。最後の闘いでサスケが一瞬こんな表情をする演出があります。“ある意味この瞬間に決着はついてるんだよ！”なんて話しながら作りました。どこなのか探してみてください。。|access-date=July 17, 2020}}</ref>

The hardware enabled a new mechanic in which the player character can receive assistance from another character with fire-<ref>{{cite web|url=https://jpgames.de/2015/07/japan-expo-2015-our-interview-with-hiroshi-matsuyama/|website=JPGames|access-date=June 28, 2020|title=Japan Expo 2015: Our interview with Hiroshi Matsuyama|date=21 July 2015|archive-date=2020-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200630031106/https://jpgames.de/2015/07/japan-expo-2015-our-interview-with-hiroshi-matsuyama/|dead-url=no}}</ref> or wood-based techniques; the details of each differ. Matsuyama noted that the implementation of running on walls was controversial among the staff; one demo focused on environmental effects, such as smoke and sand. Asked about adding Hanabi Hyuga to the cast, Matsuyama said that it would be her ''The Last: Naruto the Movie'' incarnation.<ref name="matsuyama"/>

The team researched several types of animation to improve the game's quality. [[Bleach_bypass|Bleach bypass]] was used, with reworked lighting to resemble anime; Matsuyama called it a playable anime. The game environment and the characters' facial animations were highly detailed, thanks to the new hardware. Effects were changed as well; a fire burns the victim's clothing, forcing the player to turn off the fire. Although the Shinobi world war is the focus of the story, Matsuyama also wanted the team to prioritize the final battle between Naruto and Sasuke. In early segments of the story, the team used animation from Studio Pierrot's ''Naruto Shippuden'' anime; Matsuyama said that the narrative at the beginning of the game was already well done, and the early chapters resemble anime. The team used multiple animation frames for the story mode, and Matsuyama aimed to balance the game's visuals with Pierrot's animation.<ref name="animation">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sOIp6a2ZFjA|title=Entrevista con Matsuyama-san - ''Naruto Shippuden Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' - Bandai Namco Latinoamérica|publisher=Bandai Namco Latinoamérica|date=April 5, 2015|access-date=June 29, 2020|language=es|trans-title=Interview with Matsuyama ''Naruto Shippuden Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' Latin America|archive-date=2020-09-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200911062112/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sOIp6a2ZFjA|dead-url=no}}</ref>
