''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' was announced for the PlayStation 4 in December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-announced-ps4/|title=''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' Announced For PS4|website=Siliconera|access-date=June 29, 2020|date=December 11, 2014|author=Sato|archive-date=2021-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628073008/https://www.siliconera.com/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-announced-ps4/|dead-url=no}}</ref> The game was playable by the public for the first time at [[Gamescom|Gamescom]] 2015. Originally planned for fall 2015,<ref name="matsuyamainter"/> it was announced in August of that year that the game would be delayed until February 2016<ref name="ANNDelay"/><ref name="TrueAchievements"/> to make it more authentic and up-to-date.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://in.ign.com/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4/80300/news/tgs-2015-naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-delay-explained |title=TGS 2015: ''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' Delay Explained |date=17 September 2015 |publisher=[[IGN|IGN]] |access-date=June 28, 2020 |archive-date=2021-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628061801/https://in.ign.com/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4/80300/news/tgs-2015-naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-delay-explained |dead-url=no }}</ref> The band [[Kana-Boon|Kana-Boon]] played {{nihongo|"Spiral"|スパイラル|Supairaru}}, its opening theme.<ref name="TrueAchievements">{{cite web|url=http://www.trueachievements.com/n21178/naruto-shippuden-uns4-delayed.htm |title=''Naruto Shippuden: UNS4'' Delayed |publisher=[[True_Achievements|True Achievements]] |date=August 7, 2015 |access-date=August 27, 2015}}</ref> A demo version was playable at the 2015 [[Jump_Festa|Jump Festa]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-12-16/ultimate-ninja-storm-4-game-adds-the-last-version-naruto/.82226|title=''Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' Game Adds The Last Version Naruto|website=Anime News Network|access-date=June 30, 2020|archive-date=2022-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220108034611/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-12-16/ultimate-ninja-storm-4-game-adds-the-last-version-naruto/.82226|dead-url=no}}</ref>

''Road to Boruto'', an expansion with elements from ''Boruto: Naruto the Movie'', was released on February 3, 2017; Bandai Namco Entertainment decided to end the ''Ultimate Ninja Storm'' series with it. In the patch, new versions of Naruto and Sasuke were added to a new cast: Boruto Uzumaki, Sarada Uchiha and Mitsuki.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2016/9/14/12923926/naruto-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-road-to-boruto-expansion-final-game-bandai-namco-cyberconnect2-tgs|title=This is the final ''Naruto: Ultimate Ninja'' game|first=Philip|last=Kollar|work=[[Polygon_(website)|Polygon]]|date=September 14, 2016|access-date=September 15, 2016|archive-date=2016-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916193056/http://www.polygon.com/2016/9/14/12923926/naruto-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-road-to-boruto-expansion-final-game-bandai-namco-cyberconnect2-tgs|dead-url=no}}</ref> When ''Storm 4''{{'s}} development was finished, CyberConnect2 began work on [[Downloadable_content|DLC]] in response to the favorable response to ''Boruto: Naruto the Movie''. The team surveyed players about what they wanted to play in the game, and most responses involved [[Boruto_Uzumaki|Boruto Uzumaki]]'s generation. Matsuyama thought that Boruto's main story would take three or four hours, and side stories were created to increase game length. Although this DLC was intended as the ''Storm'' series' final chapter,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shonengamez.com/2016/12/18/famitsu-road-to-boruto-interview-takes-3-4-hours-to-finish-no-plans-to-add-dlc-to-dlc/|title=Famitsu ''Road to Boruto'' Interview: Takes 3-4 Hours to Finish, No Plans to "Add DLC to DLC"|date=December 18, 2016|access-date=June 29, 2020|archive-date=2022-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220105064618/https://shonengamez.com/2016/12/18/famitsu-road-to-boruto-interview-takes-3-4-hours-to-finish-no-plans-to-add-dlc-to-dlc/|dead-url=no}}</ref> other DLC (side stories focused on [[Gaara|Gaara]] and [[Shikamaru_Nara|Shikamaru Nara]]) was released in March 2016.<ref name="expansion">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/videos/2016/03/29/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-official-gaaras-tale-trailer|title=''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' Official Gaara's Tale Trailer|website=IGN|date=March 29, 2016|access-date=June 28, 2020|archive-date=2021-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628065944/https://www.ign.com/videos/2016/03/29/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-official-gaaras-tale-trailer|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="expansiontwo">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/videos/2016/03/01/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-official-shikamarus-tale-trailer|title=''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' Official Shikamaru's Tale Trailer|website=IGN|date=March 1, 2016|access-date=June 28, 2020|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629184050/https://www.ign.com/videos/2016/03/01/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-official-shikamarus-tale-trailer|dead-url=no}}</ref> Additional DLC was "Virtual Reality", in which Boruto can fight strong bosses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shonengamez.com/2017/01/18/road-to-boruto-virtual-reality-sub-story-announced/|title=''Road to Boruto'' Virtual Reality Sub-Story Announced|website=Shonen Gamez|date=January 18, 2017|access-date=June 28, 2020|archive-date=2022-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220105065727/https://shonengamez.com/2017/01/18/road-to-boruto-virtual-reality-sub-story-announced/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

A patch for the PC version, giving the game a 60-FPS [[frame_rate|frame rate]], was released in February 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-pc-patch-unlocks-60fps/|title=''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' PC Patch Unlocks 60fps|website=Siliconera|access-date=June 28, 2020|date=February 6, 2017|author=Lada, Jenn|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629143532/https://www.siliconera.com/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-pc-patch-unlocks-60fps/|dead-url=no}}</ref> A [[Nintendo_Switch|Nintendo Switch]] port was announced and a Next Generations DLC pack for all platforms, with new playable characters and costumes from the ''[[Boruto:_Naruto_Next_Generations|Boruto: Naruto Next Generations]]'' anime series, was announced in December 2019. The pack included Kinshiki and Momoshiki Ōtsutsuki as playable characters<ref name="NextGenerations">{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-17/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-road-to-boruto-game-heads-west-for-switch-on-april-24/.154453 |title=''Naruto Shippūden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4 Road to Boruto'' Game Heads West for Switch on April 24 |publisher=[[Anime_News_Network|Anime News Network]] |date=December 16, 2019 |access-date=December 17, 2019}}</ref> and adult skins from other supporting characters.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://naruto-game.bn-ent.net//special/nsw.html|title=Nintendo Switch|website=Naruto Game BN|access-date=June 30, 2020|archive-date=2021-06-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210625151658/https://naruto-game.bn-ent.net//special/nsw.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> Matsuyama said that porting the game to Switch was Bandai's decision, rather than his, until CyberConnect2 approved it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nextn.es/2019/12/naruto-storm-4-road-to-boruto-switch-2020/|title=Naruto Storm 4: ''Road To Boruto'' Por Fin Llegará a Switch en 2020|website=Nextn|date=December 2019|access-date=June 28, 2020|language=es|trans-title=Naruto Storm 4: ''Road To Boruto'' finally reaches the Swtich in 2020|archive-date=2021-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628062420/https://www.nextn.es/2019/12/naruto-storm-4-road-to-boruto-switch-2020/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
