=== 銷售 ===
{{TransH}}
''Storm 4'' sold a chart-topping 64,446 copies in Japan for the PlayStation 4, exceeding the launch sales of the first two ''Storm'' games but failing to reach those of ''Storm 3''. According to the ''[[Siliconera|Siliconera]]'' website, the lower sales may have been related to ''Storm 4''{{'s}} release after the manga ended its serialization (unlike the previous games).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/week-sales-naruto-takes-top-20-storm-dattebayo/|title=This Week In Sales: Naruto Takes The Top-20 By Storm, Dattebayo!|publisher=Siliconera|access-date=June 28, 2020|archive-date=2017-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170612002417/http://www.siliconera.com/2016/02/10/week-sales-naruto-takes-top-20-storm-dattebayo/|dead-url=no}}</ref> A Bandai Namco press release reported in February 2016 that ''Storm 4'' had shipped 1,334,000 copies worldwide: 80,000 in Japan, 84,000 elsewhere in Asia, 550,000 in Europe, and 620,000 in North America.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siliconera.com/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-ships-1-3-million-units-worldwide/|title=''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' Ships Over 1.3 Million Units Worldwide|website=Siliconera|date=February 8, 2016|author=Sato|access-date=June 28, 2020|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629185718/https://www.siliconera.com/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-ships-1-3-million-units-worldwide/|dead-url=no}}</ref> ''VentureBeat'' found it as one of the top-selling fighting games during its release rivaled only by [[Capcom|Capcom]]'s ''[[Street_Fighter_V|Street Fighter V]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/03/10/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-outsold-street-fighter-v-on-playstation-4/|title=''Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' nearly outsold ''Street Fighter V'' on PlayStation 4 (correction)|website=VentureBeat|date=March 10, 2016|author=Grubb, Jeff|access-date=November 2, 2020|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111173115/https://venturebeat.com/2016/03/10/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-outsold-street-fighter-v-on-playstation-4/|dead-url=no}}</ref> In June 2016, TV Tokyo announced that the game had sold over 1.5 million copies worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2016-06-10/tv-tokyo-most-profitable-anime-april-2015-to-march-2016/.102927|title=TV Tokyo's Most Profitable Anime: April 2015 to March 2016|publisher=Anime News Network|access-date=June 10, 2016|archive-date=2019-11-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191110074036/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2016-06-10/tv-tokyo-most-profitable-anime-april-2015-to-march-2016/.102927|dead-url=no}}</ref> On September 12 of that year, [[Bandai_Namco_Entertainment|Bandai Namco Entertainment]] announced that ''Storm 4'' had shipped two million copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-12/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-road-to-boruto-update-detailed/.106350|title=''Naruto Shippūden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4{{'}}s Road to Boruto'' Update Detailed|date=September 12, 2016|access-date=September 15, 2016|work=[[Anime_News_Network|Anime News Network]]|archive-date=2019-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004022142/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-12/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-road-to-boruto-update-detailed/.106350|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

The expansion ''Road to Boruto'' sold 9,204 units in Japan which was considered as a strong number by ''Siliconera'' due it being DLC.<ref>{{cite web|title=This Week In Sales: Road to Boruto Releases In Japan, Dattebasa|url=https://www.siliconera.com/week-sales-road-boruto-releases-japan-dattebasa/|website=Siliconera|date=February 8, 2017|author=Sato|access-date=November 1, 2020|archive-date=2020-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204024426/https://www.siliconera.com/week-sales-road-boruto-releases-japan-dattebasa/|dead-url=no}}</ref> In November 2017, it was announced that the combined shipments of the original game, ''Road to Boruto'' and digital sales had reached three million copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-11-02/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-game-worldwide-shipments-download-sales-hit-3-million/.123501|title=Naruto Shippūden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4 Game's Worldwide Shipments, Download Sales Hit 3 Million|date=November 2, 2017|access-date=November 2, 2017|work=[[Anime_News_Network|Anime News Network]]|archive-date=2019-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190520113906/https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-11-02/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-game-worldwide-shipments-download-sales-hit-3-million/.123501|dead-url=no}}</ref> During a live stream CyberConnect2 announced that ''Storm 4'' including ''Road to Boruto'' had sold 5.8 million copies by March 2020.<ref name="total">{{cite web|url=https://www.kitguru.net/gaming/uncategorized/mustafa-mahmoud/ultimate-ninja-storm-4-becomes-one-of-the-best-selling-fighting-games-this-generation/|title=''Ultimate Ninja Storm 4'' becomes one of the best selling fighting games this generation|website=Kitguru|access-date=February 8, 2021|archive-date=2021-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210301173955/https://www.kitguru.net/gaming/uncategorized/mustafa-mahmoud/ultimate-ninja-storm-4-becomes-one-of-the-best-selling-fighting-games-this-generation/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://xbox-mag.net/2020/03/28/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-road-boruto-approche-des-six-millions-dunites-ecoulees/|title=Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja Storm 4 – Road to Boruto approche des six millions d'unités écoulées|website=Xbox Magazine|date=March 28, 2020|access-date=February 8, 2021|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629183705/https://xbox-mag.net/2020/03/28/naruto-shippuden-ultimate-ninja-storm-4-road-boruto-approche-des-six-millions-dunites-ecoulees/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
